net.markenwerk.commons.interfaces

Interface Predicate<Subject>

  • Type Parameters:
    Subject - The type of the values to perform tests on.

    public interface Predicate<Subject>
    A Predicate is used to perform arbitrary test on test subject. It is usually used in a scenario where some sort of data provider wants to offer the possibility to filter values before delivery or during the data processing.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

    • Method Detail

      • test

        boolean test(Subject subject)
      throws EvaluationException
        Performs the test on a given test subject.

        It lies in the responsibility of the caller, to handle unwanted null-values by replacing them with a sensible default value or throwing a NullPointerException.

        Implementers should catch any exception and wrap them in a EvaluationException.

        Parameters:
        subject - The test subject.
        Returns:
        Whether the test subject passed the test.
        Throws:
        EvaluationException - If testing the test subject failed.
